            <abstract><p>Sending Smith a parcel containing specimens of the Indian breadroot and first two numbers of [Stephen] Elliott's "Sketch of the botany of South Carolina and Georgia". During his journey from east Florida he met Dr [William] Baldwin, "a very intelligent botanist &amp; indefatigable traveller", who has given him a letter and parcel of specimens to forward to Smith on his return.</p></abstract>
